The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 May is 42,128 (4,876 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 09 May, there were 123 new confirmed cases (14.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 May, there were 114 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 8% (9 extra cases).
